 from the main page.  This is the most basic of React applications, but we can already see some things we may not have seen before.  The 
import
 statements bring in ES2015 modules for use.  Also, you can embed pseudo-HTML into a React application rendering method by using 
JSX
.  When the application is transpiled with BabelJS, this pseudo-HTML get compiled into normal JavaScript.


There are three other files we want to produce that are build related.  The first is the 
.babelrc
 file.  This contains instructions to the BabelJS transpiler that tells it what specifications need to be transpiled:


